OL,3,CFormer Post Office boss says he's
OL,4,C'subject of a smear campaign' by
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FAfter Mr Staunton claimed he had been
OL,8,Ftold by a civil servant to go slow on
OL,9,Fcompensation payments ahead of the
OL,10,Felection, Ms Badenoch said he was
OL,11,Flying and that his comments were "a
OL,12,Fblatant attempt to seek revenge" for
OL,13,Fbeing sacked.
OL,15,FWhen asked about how it felt to be
OL,16,Fcalled a liar by a senior politician,
OL,17,FMr Staunton said: "I don't want to
OL,18,Fblow my own trumpet, but I've been the
OL,19,Fchairman of four big companies."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/14
