OL,3,CFormer Post Office boss says he's
OL,4,C'subject of a smear campaign' by
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FMr Byrne responded by saying: "I think
OL,8,Fthe committee's pretty surprised
OL,9,Fyou've not had written instructions to
OL,10,Fspeed up the resolution of redress in
OL,11,Fone of the biggest miscarriages of
OL,12,Fjustice in British history."
OL,14,FComments by Mr Read sparked fury from
OL,15,Fsub-postmasters last week when in a
OL,16,Fletter to the justice secretary.
OL,18,FMr Read said the Post Office would be
OL,19,F"bound to oppose an appeal" in at
OL,20,Fleast 369 of the 700 cases it had
OL,21,Fprosecuted.
