OL,7,FWhen asked about the letter by Mr
OL,8,FGullis, Mr Read denied the letter
OL,9,Fshowed the Post Office wanted to block
OL,10,Fthe mass exoneration law - saying he
OL,11,Fwas just making sure the government
OL,12,Fhad all the available information
OL,13,Fbefore it legislated.
OL,15,FMr Read also insisted the culture of
OL,16,Fthe Post Office is changing after Alan
OL,17,FBates said it "will not change".
